<div class="tip_number">TIP 63</div>
<div class="tip_contents">
            If you develop a cough and/or shortness of breath after surgery—even a week or two afterward—you may have a blood clot in your lung, or pneumonia. You are particularly at risk if you first noticed swelling and tenderness in the back of your lower leg or in your groin, where a clot could have originated before traveling in the veins to your lung.
        </div>

</div>
